      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes a new optional type of OSPF area, somewhat humorously referred to as a "not-so-stubby" area (or NSSA).  NSSAs are similar to the existing OSPF stub area configuration option but have the additional capability of importing AS external routes in a limited fashion. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
